local extensions = require("extensions")
local limits = self.pinIn.limits.value
local idtable = self.pinIn.idtable.value
local laps = self.pinIn.laps.value
local mode = self.pinIn.speedMode.value
local lane = self.pinIn.useLanes.value
local risk = self.pinIn.risk.value
local avoid = self.pinIn.avoid.value == 1
local speed = self.pinIn.routeSpd.value
local codrivability = self.pinIn.codrivability.value
local wpspd = self.pinIn.wpspd.value
local wtable = self.pinIn.waypoints.value
local count = #wtable
local spdtable = {}
local spdsplit = {}
local spdtfirst = false

local cwp = ""
local clim = 0

local args = "{"

if laps ~= nil then
args = args .. "noOfLaps = " .. laps .. ","
end

if lane ~= nil then
args = args .. "driveInLane = " .. extensions.blrutils.boolToText(lane, "'on'", "'off'") .. ","
end

if avoid ~= nil then
args = args .. "avoidCars = " .. extensions.blrutils.boolToText(avoid, "'on'", "'off'") .. ","
end

if risk ~= nil then
args = args .. "aggression = " .. risk .. ","
end

if speed ~= nil then
args = args .. "routeSpeed = " .. speed .. ","
end

if mode ~= nil then
args = args .. "routeSpeedMode = '" .. mode .. "',"
end

if wpspd ~= nil then
spdtable = extensions.blrutils.ssplit(wpspd, ",")
spdtfirst = true
args = args .. "wpSpeeds = {"
for k,v in pairs(spdtable) do
spdsplit = extensions.blrutils.ssplit(v, ":")
if not spdtfirst then 
args = args .. ","
else
spdtfirst = false
end
args = args .. spdsplit[1] .. "=" .. tonumber(spdsplit[2])
end
args = args .. "},"
end

args = args .. "wpTargetList = {"
for k,v in ipairs(wtable) do
args = args .. "'" .. wtable[k] .. "'"
if k ~= count then
args = args .. ","
end
end
args = args .. "}"

if limits ~= nil then
args = args .. ",wpSpeeds = {"
for k,v in ipairs(wtable) do
args = args .. wtable[k] .. "=" .. ltable[k] 
if k ~= count then
args = args .. ","
end
end
args = args .. "}"
end

args = args .. "}"

local veh = {}
for i=1,#idtable do
veh = scenetree.findObjectById(idtable[i])
if veh ~= nil then
veh:queueLuaCommand("ai.setCutOffDrivability(" .. codrivability .. ")")
-- 1.19.2 fix, looping paths with extra laps no longer turn on race mode
-- so gotta turn it on manually
veh:queueLuaCommand("ai.setRacing(true)") 
veh:queueLuaCommand("ai.driveUsingPath(" .. args .. ")")
end
end

local dtable = self.pinIn.idtable.value
local veh = {}
for k,v in pairs(dtable) do
veh = {}
if v ~= -1 then
veh = scenetree.findObjectById(v)
if veh ~= nil then
core_vehicleBridge.executeAction(veh,'setFreeze', self.pinIn.freeze.value)
end
end
end

local extensions = require("extensions")
local seed = self.pinIn.seed.value
local efile = extensions.blrutils.loadEventWithRandoms(self.pinIn.efile.value, seed)

local opModels = {}
local opConfigs = {}
local configData = efile["configs"]
-- Updated config loading, universal, works with performance class files or old config lists
local loadedConfigs = extensions.blrutils.perfclassConfigLoader(configData)
opModels = loadedConfigs["models"]
opConfigs = loadedConfigs["configs"]

local waypoints = extensions.blrutils.ssplit(efile["waypoints"],",")
waypoints[#waypoints+1] = waypoints[1]
local triggers = extensions.blrutils.ssplit(efile["triggers"],",")
local scount = tonumber(efile["scount"])
local opCount = math.min(tonumber(efile["opcount"]), self.pinIn.opt.value)
local risk = tonumber(efile["risk"]) or 1.0
local wpspd = efile["wpspd"]
local aispd = tonumber(efile["aispd"]) or 110.0
local aispdmode = efile["aispdmode"] or "limit"

local laps = tonumber(efile["laps"])

local opspos = {}
local opsrot = {}
local pspos = {}
local psrot = {}

math.randomseed(seed)
local pspawn = math.random(1,opCount+1)
pspos = extensions.blrutils.ssplitnum(efile["spos" .. pspawn],",")
psrot = extensions.blrutils.ssplitnum(efile["srot" .. pspawn],",")

local padded = false
for i=1,opCount do
padded = i==pspawn or padded
if not padded then
opspos[i] = efile["spos" .. i]
opsrot[i] = efile["srot" .. i]
else
opspos[i] = efile["spos" .. i+1]
opsrot[i] = efile["srot" .. i+1]
end
end

self.pinOut.opModels.value = opModels
self.pinOut.opConfigs.value = opConfigs
self.pinOut.pspos.value = pspos
self.pinOut.psrot.value = psrot
self.pinOut.waypoints.value = waypoints
self.pinOut.triggers.value = triggers
self.pinOut.opCount.value = opCount
self.pinOut.opspos.value = opspos
self.pinOut.opsrot.value = opsrot
self.pinOut.laps.value = laps
self.pinOut.cpcount.value = #triggers
self.pinOut.wpspd.value = wpspd
self.pinOut.aispd.value = aispd
self.pinOut.aispdmode.value = aispdmode
self.pinOut.risk.value = risk

local dtable = self.pinIn.idtable.value
local veh = {}
for k,v in pairs(dtable) do
veh = {}
if v ~= -1 then
veh = scenetree.findObjectById(v)
if veh ~= nil then
core_vehicleBridge.executeAction(veh,'setFreeze', self.pinIn.freeze.value)
end
end
end

local extensions = require("extensions")
local veidtable = self.pinIn.veid.value
local nid = self.pinIn.nid.value or 0
local af = self.pinIn.af.value

local filter = -1
local tdata = {}
local statusTable = {}
local eventTable = {}
local tnameTable = {}
local tidTable = {}
local hasUpdate = false

if not extensions.blrtriggers.isNodeRegistered(nid) then
extensions.blrtriggers.registerNode(nid)
end

for k,v in pairs(veidtable) do
filter = v
tdata = extensions.blrtriggers.poolTriggerData(nid, filter, false)
if tdata then
hasUpdate = true
eventTable[filter] = tdata["event"]
tidTable[filter] = tdata["triggerID"]
tnameTable[filter] = tdata["triggerName"]
else
eventTable[filter] = nil
tidTable[filter] = nil
tnameTable[filter] = nil
end

if af == nil then
statusTable[filter] = extensions.blrtriggers.getGlobalTriggerStatus(nid,filter, false)
elseif af[filter] == nil then
statusTable[filter] = extensions.blrtriggers.getGlobalTriggerStatus(nid,filter, false)
else
statusTable[filter] = extensions.blrtriggers.getTriggerStatus(nid,filter, af[filter], false)
end

end

self.pinOut.status.value = statusTable
self.pinOut.event.value = eventTable
self.pinOut.triggerID.value = tidTable
self.pinOut.triggerName.value = tnameTable
self.pinOut.update.value = hasUpdate

local extensions = require("extensions")
local leaders = self.pinIn.leaderboard.value
local times = self.pinIn.times.value
local endpos = self.pinIn.endpos.value or -1
local winner = self.pinIn.winner.value or false
local started = self.pinIn.started.value
local toRet = ""
if started then
if leaders then
if leaders[1] then
toRet = extensions.blrlocales.translate("beamlr.generic.term.leaderboard") .. "\n"
for i=1,#leaders do
toRet = toRet .. "#" .. i .. " - " .. leaders[i] .. " " .. extensions.blrlocales.translate("beamlr.generic.term.in_lc") .. " " .. extensions.blrRaceManager.raceTimeString(extensions.blrRaceManager.msTimeFormat(times[leaders[i]])) .. "\n"
end

else
toRet = toRet .. extensions.blrlocales.translate("beamlr.imgui.meets.waitingresults")
end
else
toRet = extensions.blrlocales.translate("beamlr.imgui.track.notstarted")
end
else
toRet = extensions.blrlocales.translate("beamlr.imgui.track.notstarted")
end

if winner and started then
toRet = toRet .. "\n" .. extensions.blrlocales.translate("beamlr.imgui.track.racewon")
elseif endpos ~= -1 and started then
toRet = toRet .. "\n" .. extensions.blrlocales.translate("beamlr.imgui.track.finishpos") .. " #" .. endpos
end

self.pinOut.strout.value = toRet

local extensions = require("extensions")
local ppos = self.pinIn.ppos.value
local seed = self.pinIn.seed.value
local efile = self.pinIn.efile.value

local rewards = {} -- For UI
rewards["moneyreward"] = 0
rewards["repreward"] = 0
rewards["partreward"] = "None"
rewards["carreward"] = "None"
local hasRewards = false -- For UI

if ppos <= 3 then -- No rewards after third position
hasRewards = true -- For UI

local edata = extensions.blrutils.loadEventWithRandoms(efile, seed)
local cdata = extensions.blrutils.loadDataTable("beamLR/mainData")




-- Money reward
if edata["moneyreward"] ~= "none" then
local money = extensions.blrutils.ssplitnum(edata["moneyreward"], ",")
cdata["money"] = tonumber(cdata["money"]) + (money[ppos] or 0) -- Should handle 1,2,3 and 1,2 and 1
rewards["moneyreward"] = (money[ppos] or 0) -- For UI
end

-- Reputation Reward
if edata["repreward"] ~= "none" then
local reputation = extensions.blrutils.ssplitnum(edata["repreward"], ",")
cdata["rep"] = tonumber(cdata["rep"]) + (reputation[ppos] or 0) -- Should handle 1,2,3 and 1,2 and 1
rewards["repreward"] = (reputation[ppos] or 0) -- For UI
end

if ppos == 1 then -- Some rewards only for first position

-- Part reward
extensions.blrPartInventory.load() -- 1.16 part inventory, load data from file
if edata["partreward"] ~= "none" then 
local parts = extensions.blrutils.ssplit(edata["partreward"], ",")
rewards["partreward"] = edata["partreward"] -- For UI
for k,v in pairs(parts) do
extensions.blrPartInventory.add(v, 0.0, 1.0, false) -- 1.16 part inventory, add part with 0 odometer, 1 integrity
end
extensions.blrPartInventory.save() -- 1.16 part inventory, save data to file
end

-- Car reward
if edata["carreward"] ~= "none" then
local cars = extensions.blrutils.ssplit(edata["carreward"], ",")
local cardata = {}
local cfirst = true
local seedoffset = 0
rewards["carreward"] = ""
for k,v in pairs(cars) do
cardata = extensions.blrutils.loadDataTable("beamLR/shop/car/" .. v)
if not cfirst then
rewards["carreward"] = rewards["carreward"] .. ", "
end
rewards["carreward"] = rewards["carreward"] .. cardata["name"] -- Using proper car name for reward display
extensions.blrutils.addShopCarToGarage(v, tonumber(cdata["carCount"] or "0"), seed+seedoffset)
cdata["carCount"] = tonumber(cdata["carCount"] or "0") + 1
cfirst=false
seedoffset=seedoffset+1
end
end

end


extensions.blrutils.updateDataTable("beamLR/mainData", cdata)


-- 1.17.5 storing event results 
local results = extensions.blrutils.loadDataTable("beamLR/trackEventResults", true)
local append = edata["title"] .. "," .. edata["layout"] .. "," .. ppos .. "," .. rewards["moneyreward"] .. "," .. rewards["repreward"] .. "," .. rewards["partreward"] .. "," .. rewards["carreward"]
table.insert(results, append)
extensions.blrutils.saveDataTable("beamLR/trackEventResults", results)
end

self.pinOut.rewards.value = rewards
self.pinOut.hasRewards.value = hasRewards

local extensions = require("extensions")

dtable["status"] = "over"

local extensions = require("extensions")

local extensions = require("extensions")
extensions.blrglobals.blrFlagSet(self.pinIn.name.value, self.pinIn.flag.value)

local extensions = require("extensions")
local im = ui_imgui
local enabled = self.pinIn.enabled.value and (extensions.blrglobals.blrFlagGet("imToggle") or self.pinIn.ignoreToggle.value)
local avail = im.GetContentRegionAvail()
-- Confirmable button vars
local confirm = self.pinIn.confirm.value
local cid = self.pinIn.cid.value
local cstate = false
local ccancel = self.pinIn.ccancel.value -- Cancel action linked to a confirmable button to reset confirm state on click
local clink = self.pinIn.clink.value
-- Mouse states
local down = false
local hold = false
local up = false

-- Button display
if confirm then
cstate = extensions.blrutils.getButtonConfirm(cid)
if cstate then
im.Button(extensions.blrlocales.translate("beamlr.generic.button.confirm")  ..'##'.. tostring(self.id), im.ImVec2(avail.x, 0))
else
im.Button(extensions.blrlocales.translate(tostring(self.pinIn.text.value or "Button"))  ..'##'.. tostring(self.id), im.ImVec2(avail.x, 0))
end
else
im.Button(extensions.blrlocales.translate(tostring(self.pinIn.text.value or "Button"))  ..'##'.. tostring(self.id), im.ImVec2(avail.x, 0))
end

-- Button logic
if enabled then
if im.IsItemHovered() then

down = im.IsMouseClicked(0)
hold = im.IsMouseDown(0)
up =   im.IsMouseReleased(0)
if (down or hold or up) then
if down then hold = false up = false end
if hold then down = false up = false end
if up then down = false hold = false end
end

if confirm then -- Confirmable button
if cstate then
self.pinOut.down.value = down
self.pinOut.hold.value = hold
self.pinOut.up.value = up
if down then 
extensions.blrutils.cycleButtonConfirm(cid) 
if ccancel and clink then -- Confirmable button cancel link where cancel button is also confirmable
extensions.blrutils.setButtonConfirm(clink, false)
end
end
else
if down then 
extensions.blrutils.cycleButtonConfirm(cid) 
end
end

else -- Regular button
self.pinOut.down.value = down
self.pinOut.hold.value = hold
self.pinOut.up.value = up

if down and ccancel and clink then -- Confirmable button cancel link
extensions.blrutils.setButtonConfirm(clink, false)
end

end

else -- Button not hovered
self.pinOut.down.value = false
self.pinOut.hold.value = false
self.pinOut.up.value = false
end

else -- Button not enabled
self.pinOut.down.value = false
self.pinOut.hold.value = false
self.pinOut.up.value = false
end

local extensions = require("extensions")
local dtable = extensions.blrutils.loadDataTable("beamLR/currentTrackEvent")
local seed = tonumber(dtable["seed"])
local efile = dtable["efile"]
local etable = extensions.blrutils.loadEventWithRandoms(efile, tonumber(seed))
local cround = tonumber(dtable["cround"])
local rbseed = (etable["rbseed"] or "false") == "true"
if rbseed then seed = seed + cround end -- round based seed, to get different opponents on RoH event
local cmap = extensions.blrutils.getLevelName()
local tmap = etable["map"]
local status = dtable["status"]
local prefabs = etable["prefabs"] or "none" -- 1.17.1 prefabs

local leaderboard = extensions.blrutils.ssplit(dtable["ctimes"], ",")

local bossmode = etable["bossevent"] == "true"

local carid = tonumber(dtable["carid"])

local espos = extensions.blrutils.ssplitnum(etable["espos"], ",")
local esrot = extensions.blrutils.ssplitnum(etable["esrot"], ",")

local opcount = tonumber(etable["opcount"])
local pname = extensions.blrutils.loadDataTable("beamLR/options")["playername"]

elseif v ~= 1 then -- Racer had finished, use actual time
finaltimes[v] = times[k]
end
if finaltimes[v] > worstfinal then -- Detects new worst time
worstfinal = finaltimes[v] -- In case player has DNF to give even worse time than worst AI
end
end

-- Deal with player time
if not times[pid] then
finaltimes[1] = worstfinal * 2 -- Player DNF, use worst opponent time * 2
else

end
